    "Immunohistochemical stain for BerEP4 was positive in the small cells component, while the polygonal cells component stained for epithelial membrane antigen (EMA).",
    "proliferation index was less than 1%.",
    "A 12-year-old male presented with a chalky and long-standing 1.5 cm nodule on the left cheek.",
    "Following dermatological examination, the lesion was excised.",
    "On histology, hematoxylin&eosin stain demonstrated a multilobulated proliferation in the dermis composed of small cells with basophilic cytoplasm and brisk mitotic activity, mainly arranged at the periphery of solid nodules."
